  "body": "`Part of #9264 keycard sign-in epic (mark as checked there, when closing this issue)`\r\n\r\nWe should display the number of attempts if it's less than three to warn the user. The number of attempts **should be displayed after the \"Wrong passcode\" message** flashes, not overlap it. Here's a video of how it should work:\r\n\r\n<img width=\"256\" alt=\"screen1\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/3115606/67675996-8b226b00-f9bb-11e9-8428-ee89e44fe6f2.gif\">\r\n\r\nStatic image:\r\n<img width=\"1153\" alt=\"Untitled5\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/3115606/67676507-9d50d900-f9bc-11e9-97e9-b81577a331c1.png\">\r\n\r\nFigma:\r\nhttps://www.figma.com/file/dEIljL7UPbXgsZUA0Q4qlE5E/Onboarding?node-id=4566%3A12\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n**Bonus**\r\nIt would be even cooler and a much better experience for the user if we add a more verbose warning when there's only one attempt left, with \"Help\" link in it to open a popup explaining what a \"Frozen key\" is. This could be the next iteration of this issue. cc @guylouis \r\n\r\nImage:\r\n<img width=\"425\" alt=\"last-attempt\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/3115606/67837499-26395300-fb2a-11e9-8243-948f942b9930.png\">\r\n\r\n",
